org.ingatan.io
Class ZipTools

java.lang.Object
  org.ingatan.io.ZipTools

public class ZipTools
extends java.lang.Object

Methods for accessing and writing zip files. Zip files are the basis of the library filtype used by Ingatan. The methods within this class do not handle directories within zip files.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Thomas Everingham

Method Detail

createZip

public static void createZip(java.lang.String[] filenames,
                             java.lang.String zipDestination)
                      throws java.io.IOException
Creates a new zip file at the specified destination containing all of the specified files. Resulting zip contains only the files, does not construct any directories.

Parameters:
filenames - the files to be included within the zip file.
zipDestination - where to save the newly created zip file.
Throws:
java.io.IOException - when there is a problem writing the zip to the specified location.

createZip

public static void createZip(java.io.File[] files,
                             java.io.File zipDestination)
                      throws java.io.IOException
Convenience method which takes an array of File objects rather than an array of Strings. The array is simply converted to an array of String file paths and then passed to createZip(String[], String).

Parameters:
files - the array of files to include in the zip.
zipDestination - the destination of the created zip file.
Throws:
java.io.IOException

unzip

public static void unzip(java.lang.String zipFilename,
                         java.lang.String destinationPath)
                  throws java.io.IOException
Unzip the specified zip file into the destination path.

Parameters:
zipFilename - the zip file to extract.
destinationPath - the path into which the zip files should be created.
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if there is a problem accessing the zip file or writing the extracted files

extractSingleFile

public static void extractSingleFile(java.lang.String zipFilename,
                                     java.lang.String fileToExtract,
                                     java.lang.String extractTo)
                              throws java.io.IOException
Extracts a single file from the specified zip, and writes it to the specified directory.

Parameters:
zipFilename - the zip from whcih to extract the file.
fileToExtract - the name of the file to be extracted within the zip file. You may use the existsInZip method to ensure that the file exists within the zip file.
extractTo - Path of the destination of the extracted file. Do not include the file name.
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if there is a problem accessing the zip file or writing the extracted file

getZipFileList

Gets the list of files contained by the zip file.

Parameters:
zipFileName - the zip file from which the file list should be retreived.
Returns:
String array of the files contained by the zip file.
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if the zip file at 'zipFileName' could not be accessed.

existsInZip

public static boolean existsInZip(java.lang.String filename,
                                  java.lang.String zipFileName)
                           throws java.io.IOException
Checks to see whether the specified filename exists within the specified zip file.

Parameters:
filename - the file that may or may not exist within the zip file.
zipFileName - the zip file to check.
Returns:
true if the file 'filename' exists as an entry within the zip file located at 'zipFileName'.
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if the zip at 'zipFileName' cannot be accessed.
